{"type":"message","id":"63e78675","parentId":"443d8a49","timestamp":"2026-03-16T06:35:39.327Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Clarifying group chat notifications**\n\nI see the user is asking if they need to \"at\" me every time for messages to come through in a group chat. It seems like the safest assumption is yes, unless I'm specifically set up to read all messages. I might need to check the documentation to confirm this. My earlier search didn't go well, so I'll try to narrow it down and look specifically for rules about mentioned messages in group chats. Let's keep searching!","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_EGJy85JjKDiXISnELtP77PEf","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"find /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/docs -type f \\( -name '*.md' -o -name '*.mdx' -o -name '*.json' -o -name '*.yaml' -o -name '*.yml' \\) -print0 | xargs -0 grep -nE \"was_mentioned|mentioned|mention|group chat|群聊|at你|@机器人|机器人\" 2>/dev/null | head -n 80","workdir":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace","timeout":20}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"gmn","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773642926903}}
